I had no thoughts at firſt of publiſhing any thing on this Subject, becauſe there is a great deal to this purpoſe already printed in

                  Mr. Gurnal's Chriſtian Warfare. Mr. Swinnock's Chriſtian Man's Calling. Mr. Baxter's Directory. Yet Supplem. to the Morning-Exerciſe at Cripplegate. Some of Dr. Manton's Sermons. Mr. O.H's Family-Altar, &c. other Practical Books, from whence I have had Aſſiſtance;

and ſome others of my Brethren, I did hope would be prevailed with to print their Sermons, (and am glad to hear that it is now doing, or reſolved to be done.) But you, and others who do conſtantly attend my Miniſtry, do hope to profit further by the Peruſal of thoſe things, which in the Delivery were of ſome uſe.
